-- Taiwan Equity Movers: Phison Electronics, Powertech, Shin Kong
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-03-02T07:10:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/taiwan-equity-movers-phison-electronics-powertech-shin-kong.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index gained 0.3 percent to 8,144.04,
the highest close since Aug. 4. The market will trade tomorrow
to compensate for a holiday earlier this week.  Phison Electronics Corp. (8299)  (8299 TT), an integrated circuit
maker, gained 3.6 percent to NT$247, the biggest advance since
Feb. 13. The company’s share-price estimate was raised 47
percent to NT$250 at KGI Securities Co.  Powertech Technology Inc. (6239)  (6239 TT) sank 6.4 percent to
NT$58.70, the lowest close since June 23, 2009. Japan’s Elpida
Corp. applied for bankruptcy this week. Powertech estimated it
has NT$2 billion ($68 million) of net receivables from Elpida,
according to a statement to the local stock exchange.  Shin Kong Financial Holding Co. (2888)  (2888 TT) increased 1.5
percent to NT$10.15, the highest close since Feb. 15. The
financial services company’s life insurance unit got a $100-
million quota to invest as a Qualified Foreign Institutional
Investor from  China ’s State Administration of Foreign Exchange,
according to a Shin Kong statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
